edu.cmu.ri.rcommerce.filter
Class DoubleThresholdPeakDetector

java.lang.Object
  edu.cmu.ri.rcommerce.filter.DoubleThresholdPeakDetector

public class DoubleThresholdPeakDetector
extends Object

An online peak detector that accumulates data and looks for a peak when requested. Alternately waits for highThreshold and lowThreshold values and reports a peak when 'cooldown' amount of milliseconds have passed and the current value in the buffer is past the threshold.

Constructor Detail

DoubleThresholdPeakDetector

public DoubleThresholdPeakDetector(double lowThreshold,
                                   double highThreshold,
                                   long cooldown)
Create a peak detector filter.

Parameters:
lowThreshold - after the signal passes the high threshold, it waits for this threshold before reporting another peak
highThreshold - after the signal passes the low threshold, it waits for this threshold before reporting another peak
cooldown - the amount of time after a peak that additional peaks are suppressed.

public boolean foundPeak()
Look in the buffer until it finds a peak. Remove all the values up to the peak and return true. If a peak cannot be found, return false
